# Agent Boundaries

## Always apply

- **Zero Placeholder Policy:** Never leave incomplete code or `// TODO` stubs. Deliver fully functional units of work.
- **Anti-Hallucination:** Verify the existence of npm packages via the terminal before suggesting imports.
- **Interface-First Development:** Define TypeScript interfaces and types before writing implementation code.
- **Security First:** Do not hardcode API keys. API keys must remain in `.env` (gitignored) and be accessed via `import.meta.env` in Vite.
- **Supabase anon default-deny:** New `public` tables must not retain default **`anon`** privileges; **`REVOKE`** from **`anon`** (at least `SELECT`) after grants unless anonymous access is explicitly requested.
- **Inspect Before Acting:** Do not assume scripts (`npm run build`, `npm run test:unit`, etc.) or planned directories (`src/`, `supabase/`, `docs/`) exist. Verify the repo state before invoking them or referencing them in code.
- **Dependency Management:** Install new npm packages only if they are lightweight utilities (e.g. `lucide-react`, `date-fns`). Never install competing heavy frameworks (e.g. another state management library over Zustand).
- **Destructive Actions:** Never force-push (`git push -f`), hard-reset, rebase, or delete operational root configurations unless explicitly instructed.

## During `/lfg` or explicit autonomous runs

Applies when the user invokes `/lfg`, an LFG pipeline run, or AGENTS.md autonomous execution. See [`.cursor/rules/05-lfg-guardrails.mdc`](.cursor/rules/05-lfg-guardrails.mdc) for the full checklist.

- **Branch creation:** Create a feature branch from `main` before implementation (`git pull origin main` first). Never work on `main` for feature code.
- **Branch naming:**
  - Issue-linked: `{type}/{issue}-{slug}` (pattern: type, issue number, kebab slug)
  - No issue: `{type}/{slug}`
  - `type` from plan frontmatter (`feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `perf`)
  - `slug`: lowercase kebab-case, max 40 characters, derived from plan title
  - Forbidden: `main`, opaque auto-generated names, mid-run branch switches
- **No branch prompts:** Do not ask to continue on the current branch or create a new one — create the branch per the rules above.
- **Commit freedom:** Auto-commit per FSD layer or logical segment; use Conventional Commits.
- **Push and PR:** Push the branch and open a PR at ship; include `Closes #N` when the plan has `issue: N`.

## Outside LFG

- **Git safety:** No destructive git operations; no commit unless the user explicitly requests it.
- **Branching:** Do not checkout or create a new branch unless the user explicitly requests it.
